\nI need to inspect files for version 2.13.4 to check if there are any necessary copy edits. However, the user specified that they only need changes for version 2.21.0, so I'll focus on that. I'll likely just change the active version and might need to use a single edit call for the Java file. Since it's small, I could rewrite the entire file, but it seems better to make precise changes as per instructions. I should also inspect the git status before finalizing my commit, even if it's not strictly necessary.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Creating a new test file**\\n\\nI’m working on a new test file where I need to remove the `java.awt.Point` import and add a test called `populatesFieldOnlyProperties`. In this test, I’ll create a `FieldBackedReaderBean` instance from a JSON string to check if the name is populated correctly. I’m considering keeping the field public, hence no getter is necessary. I’ll also modify the classes to include public and private setter tests. \\n\\nI should define a new `FieldBackedReaderBean` class with the necessary fields and a no-argument constructor. It seems that JUnit methods can be package-private, which is fine. I’m still pondering whether to use `JSON_WITH_FORCE_ACCESS` for a public field. Though using `JSON.std` could be consistent, I’ll focus on metadata insertion at the top before the PublicSetter entry. Time to start editing!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XqszmhSuB2RwFEwGY1LKq1Ps|fc_043c32675d148b610169f02c33627881a1b955c981101b06ca", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.fasterxml.jackson.jr/jackson-jr-objects/2.21.0/src/test/java/com_fasterxml_jackson_jr/jackson_jr_objects/BeanPropertyReaderDynamicAccessTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.awt.Point;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.jr.ob.JSON;\n", "newText": "import com.fasterxml.jackson.jr.ob.JSON;\n"}, {"oldText": "    void populatesFieldBackedJdkBeanProperties() throws Exception {\n        Point point = JSON_WITH_FORCE_ACCES