he developer mentioned that rewrites are allowed for new files or complete rewrites, which fits my situation. However, I can also edit it precisely if needed. I might replace the whole content, but I need to consider the package-private top-level as well. Good thing the public class is already in place, making it easier to move forward.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class usage**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether to leave the private setter bean class unused. It might be stale, but it seems acceptable. The user wants to focus on the active class only, and keeping that unused extra bean could preserve resource validity. However, if there’s no JSON path referencing them, then dynamic access coverage isn’t affected. I guess that’s fine, but I want to make sure I’m clear about the user’s intentions regarding this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nXjTOpQ0uHJNwK39DBvaUkLh|fc_043c32675d148b610169f02cc7683881a1a22dc31a420415df", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.fasterxml.jackson.jr/jackson-jr-objects/2.21.0/src/test/java/com_fasterxml_jackson_jr/jackson_jr_objects/BeanPropertyReaderDynamicAccessTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "package com_fasterxml_jackson_jr.jackson_jr_objects;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.jr.ob.JSON;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class BeanPropertyReaderDynamicAccessTest {\n    private static final JSON JSON_WITH_FORCE_ACCESS = JSON.std.with(JSON.Feature.FORCE_REFLECTION_ACCESS);\n\n    @Test\n    void populatesFieldOnlyProperties() throws Exception {\n        FieldBackedReaderBean bean = JSON_WITH_FORCE_ACCESS.beanFrom(FieldBackedReaderBean.class,\n                \"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Ada\\\"}\");\n\n        assertThat(bean.name).isEqualTo(\"Ada\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void populatesPublicSetterBackedProperties() throws Exception {\n        PublicSetterBackedReaderBean bean = JSON_WITH_FORCE_ACCESS.beanFrom(PublicSetterBackedReaderBean.class,\n                \"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Ada\\\"}\");\n\n        assertThat(bean.getName()).isEqualTo(\"Ada\");\n        assertThat(bean.getSetterCalls()).isEqualTo(1);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void populatesPrivateSetterBackedProperties() throws Exception {\n        SetterBackedReaderBean bean = JSON_WITH_FORCE_ACCESS.beanFrom(SetterBackedReaderBean.class,\n                \"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Ada\\\"}\");\n\n        assertThat(bean.getName()).isEqualTo(\"Ada\");\n        assertThat(bean.getSetterCalls()).isEqualTo(1);\n    }\n", "newText": "package com_fasterxml_jackson_jr.jackson_jr_objects;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\n\nimport com.fasterxml.jackson.jr.ob.impl.BeanPropertyReader;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class BeanPropertyReaderDynamicAccessTest {\n    @Test\n    void setsValuesThroughFieldBackedProperties() throws Exception {\n        Field field = FieldBackedReaderBean.class.getField(\"name\");\n        BeanPropertyReader reader = new BeanPropertyReader(\"name\", field, null, -1);\n        FieldBackedReaderBean bean = new FieldBackedReaderBean();\n\n        reader.setValueFor(bean, new Object[]{\"Ada\"});\n\n        assertThat(bean.name).isEqualTo(\"Ada\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void setsValuesThroughSetterBackedProperties() throws Exception {\n        Method setter = PublicSetterBackedReaderBean.class.getMethod(\"setName\", String.class);\n        BeanPropertyReader reader = new BeanPropertyReader(\"name\", null, setter, -1);\n        PublicSetterBackedReaderBean bean = new PublicSetterBackedReaderBean();\n\n        reader.setValueFor(bean, new Object[]{\"Ada\"});\n\n        assertThat(bean.getName()).isEqualTo(\"Ada\");\n        assertThat(bean.getSetterCalls()).isEqualTo(1);\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.4", "usage": {"input": 859, "output": 2729, "cacheRead": 50944, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 54532, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777347758025, "responseId": "resp_043c32675d148b610169f02cae9e5c81a1a32f6d14950a0eb7"}}
